{"TopicId":118960,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Ground-baseed Camera","CreatedByName":"kerrigan778","CreatedById":102779,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-21T02:00:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerrigan778","CreatedById":102779,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-21T02:00:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThere should be a mod that automatically shows a zoomed and cropped view of your vessel as viewed from launch control or other ground observation points. Like these.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://cache1.asset-cache.net/gc/50591538-view-from-ground-up-of-space-shuttle-gettyimages.jpg?v=1\u0026amp;c=IWSAsset\u0026amp;k=2\u0026amp;d=OCUJ5gVf7YdJQI2Xhkc2QBZ1sE5JFS00jKSSyyKFb%2FAHZfOVYVNMLzLD2KCLoHSqSxeSoQDuklsV4JLh1qjP0sxgcCVtQb8Fnd%2F2A2Tq9r8%3D\u0022 alt=\u002250591538-view-from-ground-up-of-space-shuttle-gettyimages.jpg?v=1\u0026amp;c=IWSAsset\u0026amp;k=2\u0026amp;d=OCUJ5gVf7YdJQI2Xhkc2QBZ1sE5JFS00jKSSyyKFb%2FAHZfOVYVNMLzLD2KCLoHSqSxeSoQDuklsV4JLh1qjP0sxgcCVtQb8Fnd%2F2A2Tq9r8%3D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBonus points if there\u0027s some camera shake and grain. Double bonus points if it can also switch to track stage/booster separation \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://blog.al.com/space-news/2009/04/large_333987main_BI134_LH_SRB_Re_entry_444x456.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022large_333987main_BI134_LH_SRB_Re_entry_444x456.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGlamour shot:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/330/overrides/space-shuttle-discovery-final-mission-solid-rocket-boosters_33026_600x450.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022space-shuttle-discovery-final-mission-solid-rocket-boosters_33026_600x450.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThings just look cooler from a stationary viewpoint.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VenomousRequiem","CreatedById":137373,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-21T02:06:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYeah, it\u0027d be cool, sure. But I can imagine it being really hard to control the spacecraft whilst in this view. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mecripp","CreatedById":181994,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-21T02:20:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThere was Kerbal_CCTV which had a range of 2k you might look at.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mythbusters844","CreatedById":72313,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-21T02:20:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI would love a mod like this. I\u0027ve always used CameraTools to do it, but it\u0027s not immediately automatic and doesn\u0027t have camera shake or any other fancy things. It\u0027d be neat to see something like 8:52 of this:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/Vn00BvWwke0?start=532\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eand this:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/-rM1RA2Jmh8?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VenomousRequiem\u0022 data-cite=\u0022VenomousRequiem\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EYeah, it\u0027d be cool, sure. But I can imagine it being really hard to control the spacecraft whilst in this view. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe point is that it\u0027d be really cool for momentarily watching your vessel during i.e. booster separation. It\u0027s also implied that the UI (navball, etc.) would stay in this view, making control as easy as it is in-flight.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-08-21T02:31:20Z\u0022 title=\u002208/21/2015 02:31  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 21, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by mythbusters844\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yaivenov","CreatedById":81754,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-21T03:01:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VenomousRequiem\u0022 data-cite=\u0022VenomousRequiem\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EYeah, it\u0027d be cool, sure. But I can imagine it being really hard to control the spacecraft whilst in this view. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI don\u0027t know about you, but in manual flight for a rocket launch my eyes are glued to my navball and instrumentation. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}